[{"id":"cv1684","cat":"statistics","topic":"Cumulative Frequency Diagrams","q":"Because cumulative frequency is a running total of frequencies, the graph of a cumulative frequency distribution...","o":["Can never have a negative gradient","Always forms a straight line","Is always symmetrical","Always passes through the origin"],"a":0,"e":"Cumulative frequency is a running total. It can increase or stay constant as more data is added, but it can never decrease. Therefore, the gradient of the curve is never negative.","d":2,"s":"9.6"},{"id":"cv1685","cat":"statistics","topic":"Cumulative Frequency Diagrams","q":"When drawing a cumulative frequency curve, which of the following is a necessary property of the y-coordinates?","o":["They must be prime numbers","They must be equal to the class width","They must be non-decreasing as x increases","They must be decreasing as x increases"],"a":2,"e":"Since cumulative frequency is the sum of frequencies up to a certain point, the total can only increase or stay the same. This means the y-values (cumulative frequency) are non-decreasing.","d":2,"s":"9.6"},{"id":"cv1686","cat":"statistics","topic":"Cumulative Frequency Diagrams","q":"Which statement best describes the slope of a cumulative frequency curve?","o":["It is always constant","It is never negative","It is always negative","It is always zero"],"a":1,"e":"A cumulative frequency curve represents the total frequency up to each point. Because individual frequencies cannot be negative, the cumulative total can never go down, meaning the slope is always $\\ge 0$.","d":2,"s":"9.6"},{"id":"cv1687","cat":"statistics","topic":"Cumulative Frequency Diagrams","q":"The life spans of 200 light bulbs are recorded and shown on a cumulative frequency graph. What cumulative frequency value corresponds to the median life span?","o":["200","150","100","50"],"a":2,"e":"The median is the middle value of the data set. For a total frequency of N = 200, the median position is located at $\\frac{200}{2} = 100$ on the cumulative frequency axis.","d":2,"s":"9.6"},{"id":"cv1688","cat":"statistics","topic":"Cumulative Frequency Diagrams","q":"A cumulative frequency diagram represents the times of 120 athletes. At which point on the vertical axis should the median time be estimated?","o":["30","60","90","120"],"a":1,"e":"To find the median from a cumulative frequency graph, we find the middle position of the total frequency. For 120 athletes, the median position is $\\frac{120}{2} = 60$.","d":2,"s":"9.6"},{"id":"cv1689","cat":"statistics","topic":"Cumulative Frequency Diagrams","q":"The weights of 400 mangoes are plotted on a cumulative frequency curve. To find the median weight, what value should be located on the cumulative frequency axis?","o":["100","200","300","400"],"a":1,"e":"The median is the value at the $\\frac{N}{2}$ position, where N is the total frequency. Given N = 400, the median position is $\\frac{400}{2} = 200$.","d":2,"s":"9.6"}]
